Package src.main

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Blob
    Blob (or binary large object) is Omni's internal representation of a single file and its contents.
    Branch
    Branch is a wrapper around a commit and represents an individual line of development.
    Commit
    Commit is Omni's internal representation of a snapshot of a repository and its staged files at a particular point in time.
    Main
    Main brings together the classes and objects from the rest of project, allowing user inputs to be read and evaluated.
    OmniObject
    OmniObject acts as the ABC for the key Omni object types: blobs, trees, and commits.
    OmniRepo
    OmniRepo acts as the central class for the project, enabling version-control through various methods.
    Tree
    Tree is Omni's internal representation of a directory and its contents.
    Utils
